{
  "stem": "7094.3",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 12.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I arrived to the station, and I walked.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Because the station was about one and a half-- nobody recognized me, and I came.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "What happened in Sadowa Wisznia-- this was about, I don't know, a week or 10 days after that-- they were collecting the people who survived, like my mother and some other units who were in hiding and were after-- they were not taken on the train.",
      "word_count": 46
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So they were collecting these people, and they were then, uh, taking them to a ghetto in Jaworow.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "You see, they were collecting the people who survived from these little towns, where it was-- the town was made-- was going to be Judenfrei.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So they were making these towns Judenfrei, the little towns, and grouping the residue-- the people who came out of the-- who were not taken in the Final Solution, the aktion-- and putting them into a ghetto.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Our district, Jaworow, was the ghetto where they were taken.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we were waiting to go to Jaworow, because they were going-- there was a date-- I don't remember-- a week or 10 days-- to go to Jaworow.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I was staying with my mother.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You can imagine how-- when I met my mother, what kind of things there was.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "She told me that she went to our flat, which was straightaway-- you know, Ukrainians from villages came and robbed every-- and she found a photograph of me.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "She had a little photograph from school documents, and she kept it.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we were together, uh, living in, again, sort of-- they reduced the ghetto area.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It wasn't enclosed, but the area-- so the three or four houses where these people lived together.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We're talking November or end of October, 1942.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You know, then.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I was walking with my mother.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
